<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Plant 4-6 cm tall. Tuber globose, 0.5-1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-0.5 cm. Stem with 2 leaves and tubular sheaths. Leaves subopposite, lanceolate to ovate-lanceolate, subacute, 1-1.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-1.1 cm. Inflorescence terminal, 1-2-flowered; floral bract lanceolate, acuminate, 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1mm. Flowers white, sepals and petals yellowish green, 0.8-1cm across; pedicel and ovary fusiform, 6-8 mm long. Dorsal sepal ovate, obtuse, 5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5 mm; lateral sepals obliquely ovate, falcate, subacute, 6-6.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm. Petals obovoid, rounded, 3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 mm. Lip deeply 3-lobed, spurred, base quadrate, 0.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm (wide); lateral lobes oblong, rounded, 3.5-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8mm; mid-lobe oblong, rounded, 5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6 mm; spur conical, globose, rounded, curved forwards, 2-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1 mm. Column short, broad, 1 mm tall; anther-cap long-beaked, 1.5-1.9 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="flowering time">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Flowering time.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">July-September.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Terrestrial on alpine cliffs and in rock crevices at elevations of 4270-4720 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Endemic to Bhutan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
