<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Our description is based on Pearce and Cribb (2001) and an image of the holotype. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. H. Jin, Schuit., Raskoti &amp; L. Q. Huang, Cladistics" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Renz" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Herminium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Herminium albovirens" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albovirens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Herminium albovirens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName family="Orchidaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. albosanguineum" order="Asparagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="albosanguineum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. albosanguineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having yellowish-green sepals, yellowish-green to white petals and a white lip. More material of these species is needed to assess their variability.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
